    <div class="annotation">
      <h3>General Information</h3>
      <p>The first part of adding a recipe to Lattice should look very familiar. Your recipe <strong>title</strong>, <strong>servings</strong>, and <strong>ingredients</strong> can be copied exactly from whatever format they are currently in.</p>
      <p><strong>Tags</strong> are just single words that categorize or describe your recipe. These are optional, but will help other users find your recipe more easily. It is unnecessary to repeat any words that already occur in the title.</p>
      <p>Marking your recipe as <strong>secret</strong> means that you are the only user who will be able access this recipe. It will not show up in searches or the latest recipes sidebar for any other user. This also means you won't be able to see this recipe if you are signed out.</p>
